A fast-paced, humorous commercial for a futuristic kitchen gadget called the “Print Meel 3000,” a sleek countertop 3D printer that prints any food you can imagine.
Bright, colorful kitchen environments; quick comedic scenarios. Upbeat ad pacing.
• A dad requests “fried chicken” — the printer produces something that looks like a chicken-leg-shaped marshmallow. He cautiously tastes it: “Well… close enough.”
• A kid asks for “blueberry pancakes,” and the printer outputs green pancakes. The family looks confused but eats anyway.
• Quick montage of bizarre but edible creations: square spaghetti, purple hamburgers, a donut with too many holes.
VOICEOVER (female, warm, humorous):
“Introducing the Print Meel 3000 — the world’s first fully-automated food-printing companion! It can print almost any meal… usually in the right color. Results may vary. Taste may also vary. Use only as emotionally prepared.”
